public interface Set
extends TraversableCollection

interface Set Encapsulates the functionality for a set, which is defined as a type of collection that does not allow duplicate items. For now, this interface simply serves as a basis for deriving any class that is-a Set. Written by Roger West, University of Illinois at Springfield
